description:
Harry Orchard grew up on the sunny slopes of Lake Ontario, not far from Toronto. The second oldest of eight children, he helped grow produce for the city market. His father worked hard, but he ruled his family with a rough hand. His mother's tenderness and sympathy, however, soothed the hurt. Her genuine faith in God was the light and joy of the home. But what made Harry Orchard become an assassin, and how did his life dramatically change? Find out by watching our upcoming program "Harry Orchard: The Perfect Assassin."
